# CURSOR MASTER PROMPT — EnglishAI Backend

> Paste this into Cursor's project-level `.cursorrules` file or use as context when prompting.

---

## Project Identity

You are building **EnglishAI** — a production-grade AI-powered English learning platform backend.  
This is a **real portfolio project** meant to impress recruiters with advanced software engineering skills.  
Code quality, architecture discipline, and completeness matter more than speed.

---

## Tech Stack (STRICT — do not deviate)

- **Runtime**: .NET 8 / C# 12
- **Architecture**: Clean Architecture + CQRS (MediatR 12)
- **API**: ASP.NET Core 8 Minimal APIs or Controllers
- **ORM**: Entity Framework Core 8 with PostgreSQL (Npgsql)
- **Cache**: StackExchange.Redis
- **Real-time**: ASP.NET Core SignalR
- **Validation**: FluentValidation 11
- **Mapping**: Mapster (preferred) or AutoMapper
- **Auth**: JWT Bearer + Refresh Token rotation + Google OAuth
- **Logging**: Serilog + Seq sink
- **AI**: Azure Cognitive Speech SDK, OpenAI .NET SDK
- **Storage**: MinIO (dev) / Azure Blob Storage (prod)
- **Testing**: xUnit + FluentAssertions + Moq + Testcontainers + Bogus
- **Docs**: Swagger (Swashbuckle) or Scalar

---

## Solution Structure (MUST follow exactly)

```
EnglishAI.sln
├── src/
│   ├── EnglishAI.Domain/           # Entities, ValueObjects, Enums, Events, Common
│   ├── EnglishAI.Application/      # Features (CQRS), Interfaces, Behaviors, Mappings
│   ├── EnglishAI.Infrastructure/   # EF Core, Redis, AI Services, Storage, Auth
│   ├── EnglishAI.API/              # Controllers, Hubs, Middleware, Filters, Program.cs
│   └── EnglishAI.Shared/           # DTOs, Constants, Extensions
├── tests/
│   ├── EnglishAI.UnitTests/
│   ├── EnglishAI.IntegrationTests/
│   └── EnglishAI.ArchTests/
└── docker/
```

### Dependency Rule (ENFORCED)
```
Domain      → depends on NOTHING
Application → depends on Domain only
Infrastructure → depends on Application + Domain
API         → depends on Application only (never Infrastructure directly)
Shared      → depends on nothing (pure DTOs/constants)
```

---

## Coding Standards

### Naming
- **Files**: PascalCase matching class name
- **Database**: snake_case (via EF Core `UseSnakeCaseNamingConvention()`)
- **API routes**: kebab-case `/api/v1/flashcard-decks`
- **JSON responses**: camelCase

### Entity Pattern
```csharp
// Domain/Entities/Flashcard.cs
public class Flashcard : BaseAuditableEntity
{
    public Guid DeckId { get; set; }
    public string Front { get; set; } = null!;
    public string Back { get; set; } = null!;
    public string? Phonetic { get; set; }
    public string? ExampleSentence { get; set; }
    public string? AudioUrl { get; set; }
    
    // SRS fields
    public decimal EaseFactor { get; set; } = 2.5m;
    public int IntervalDays { get; set; }
    public int Repetitions { get; set; }
    public DateTime NextReviewAt { get; set; }
    public DateTime? LastReviewedAt { get; set; }
    
    // Soft delete
    public bool IsDeleted { get; set; }
    public DateTime? DeletedAt { get; set; }
    
    // Navigation
    public FlashcardDeck Deck { get; set; } = null!;
    public ICollection<FlashcardReview> Reviews { get; set; } = new List<FlashcardReview>();
}
```

### CQRS Command Pattern
```csharp
// Application/Features/{Feature}/Commands/{Action}/{Action}Command.cs
public record CreateFlashcardCommand : IRequest<FlashcardDto>
{
    public string Front { get; init; } = null!;
    public string Back { get; init; } = null!;
    public Guid DeckId { get; init; }
}

// Application/Features/{Feature}/Commands/{Action}/{Action}CommandValidator.cs
public class CreateFlashcardCommandValidator : AbstractValidator<CreateFlashcardCommand>
{
    public CreateFlashcardCommandValidator()
    {
        RuleFor(x => x.Front).NotEmpty().MaximumLength(500);
        RuleFor(x => x.Back).NotEmpty().MaximumLength(500);
        RuleFor(x => x.DeckId).NotEmpty();
    }
}

// Application/Features/{Feature}/Commands/{Action}/{Action}CommandHandler.cs
public class CreateFlashcardCommandHandler : IRequestHandler<CreateFlashcardCommand, FlashcardDto>
{
    private readonly IAppDbContext _context;
    private readonly ICurrentUserService _currentUser;
    
    // Constructor injection...
    
    public async Task<FlashcardDto> Handle(CreateFlashcardCommand request, CancellationToken ct)
    {
        // 1. Validate business rules
        // 2. Create entity
        // 3. Save
        // 4. Return DTO
    }
}
```

### CQRS Query Pattern
```csharp
// Application/Features/{Feature}/Queries/{Action}/{Action}Query.cs
public record GetDueCardsQuery : IRequest<PaginatedList<FlashcardDto>>
{
    public Guid DeckId { get; init; }
    public int Page { get; init; } = 1;
    public int PageSize { get; init; } = 20;
}
```

### Controller Pattern
```csharp
[ApiController]
[Route("api/v1/[controller]")]
[Authorize]
public class FlashcardsController : ControllerBase
{
    private readonly ISender _mediator;
    
    public FlashcardsController(ISender mediator) => _mediator = mediator;
    
    [HttpPost("{deckId}/cards")]
    [ProducesResponseType(typeof(ApiResponse<FlashcardDto>), 201)]
    [ProducesResponseType(typeof(ApiErrorResponse), 400)]
    public async Task<IActionResult> CreateCard(Guid deckId, CreateFlashcardCommand command)
    {
        command = command with { DeckId = deckId };
        var result = await _mediator.Send(command);
        return CreatedAtAction(nameof(GetCard), new { id = result.Id }, ApiResponse.Success(result));
    }
}
```

### EF Configuration Pattern
```csharp
// Infrastructure/Persistence/Configurations/FlashcardConfiguration.cs
public class FlashcardConfiguration : IEntityTypeConfiguration<Flashcard>
{
    public void Configure(EntityTypeBuilder<Flashcard> builder)
    {
        builder.ToTable("flashcards");
        builder.HasKey(f => f.Id);
        builder.Property(f => f.Front).HasMaxLength(500).IsRequired();
        builder.HasQueryFilter(f => !f.IsDeleted);
        builder.HasIndex(f => new { f.DeckId, f.NextReviewAt }).HasFilter("NOT is_deleted");
    }
}
```

---

## Pipeline Behaviors (register in this order)

1. `LoggingBehavior<,>` — log every request with timing
2. `ValidationBehavior<,>` — run FluentValidation, throw `ValidationException`
3. `PerformanceBehavior<,>` — warn if > 500ms
4. `CachingBehavior<,>` — Redis cache for queries implementing `ICacheable`
5. `TransactionBehavior<,>` — wrap commands in DB transaction

---

## API Response Wrapper

Every response uses:
```csharp
public class ApiResponse<T>
{
    public bool Success { get; set; } = true;
    public T? Data { get; set; }
    public PaginationMeta? Meta { get; set; }
}

public class ApiErrorResponse
{
    public bool Success { get; set; } = false;
    public ApiError Error { get; set; } = null!;
}

public class ApiError
{
    public string Code { get; set; } = null!;
    public string Message { get; set; } = null!;
    public Dictionary<string, string[]>? Details { get; set; }
}
```

