## When generating code, ALWAYS:

1. Follow Clean Architecture — put code in the correct layer
2. Use CQRS — every use case is a Command or Query
3. Add FluentValidation for every command
4. Use `CancellationToken` everywhere
5. Add XML doc comments on public APIs
6. Use `async/await` properly (no `.Result` or `.Wait()`)
7. Return DTOs, never entities
8. Check authorization (`_currentUser.UserId`) in handlers
9. Add proper EF indexes for query patterns
10. Log important operations with structured logging
11. Handle errors with custom exceptions
12. Write testable code (inject interfaces, not implementations)
